<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="Work.HuntingHorn"
             Title="HuntingHorn"
             BackgroundColor="#92754b">

    <ContentPage.Resources>
        <Style TargetType="Label">
            <Setter Property="TextColor" Value="White"/>
            <Setter Property="HorizontalOptions" Value="Start"/>
            <Setter Property="VerticalOptions" Value="Center"/>
            <Setter Property="FontSize" Value="16"/>
            <Setter Property="Padding" Value="10"/>
        </Style>
    </ContentPage.Resources>

    <ScrollView>
        <StackLayout Orientation="Vertical" Padding="10" Spacing="10">

            <Label Padding="10"/>
            <Image Source="hh.png" HeightRequest="300" WidthRequest="400"/>

            <Label Padding="20"/>
            <Frame BackgroundColor="#af8e5f">
                <StackLayout VerticalOptions="CenterAndExpand" Padding="5" Spacing="-15">
                    <Label Text="Guard : Unable" FontAttributes="Bold" FontSize="20"/>
                    <Label Text="Desription : " FontAttributes="Bold" FontSize="18"/>
                    <Label Text="A blunt weapon that can perform melodies that give you buffs."/>
                    <Label Text="Place Echo Bubbles to grant special effects in an area. Melody effects also benefit your allies."/>
                </StackLayout>
            </Frame>

            <Label Padding="-10"/>
            <Frame BackgroundColor="#af8e5f">
                <StackLayout VerticalOptions="CenterAndExpand" Padding="5" Spacing="-15">
                    <Label Text="Weapon Traits : " FontAttributes="Bold" FontSize="20"/>
                    <Label Text="Initially, the Hunting Horns were far weaker than the Hammer, as per the damage formula. Even attacks which the two appear to share, such as the Superpound, were weaker on the Hunting Horn."/>
                    <Label Text=""/>
                    <Label Text="Advantages : " FontAttributes="Bold" FontSize="20"/>
                    <Label Text="• Longer reach when compared to the Hammer, the other impact weapon."/>
                    <Label Text="• Whether in solo or online play, recital has an absolutely overwhelming abundance of perks, whether it be attack and defense boosts (granting both 'attacks harder to break' and higher attack strength), elemental resistances, instant health recovery, infinite stamina, immunity against extreme temperatures and even negating some status effects and tremors, in addition to nullifying monster roars."/>
                    <Label Text="• Under the effects of the self-buff note (White/Purple) Hunting Horns possess the fastest movement speed, even faster than the Sword and Shield, Light Bowgun or Dual Blades."/>
                    <Label Text="• Recital songs get even stronger in G rank."/>
                    <Label Text="• Has cutting damage by using the Forward/Hilt Stab attack. (MHP3rd onward)"/>
                    <Label Text=""/>
                    <Label Text="Limitations : " FontAttributes="Bold" FontSize="20"/>
                    <Label Text="• Its attacks are less precise than the Hammer when targeting monster weak points."/>
                    <Label Text="• Have lower KO value than the Hammer in general. Being a blunt weapon, it is normally impossible to cut tail of monsters, unless deliberately using the Hilt Stab attack."/>
                    <Label Text="• The buffs that notes provide only last for a temporary amount of time, requiring attention to maximize the benefit of the buffs throughout the hunt. Alternatively, players can use armors with the skill 'Flute Expert/Horn Maestro' to somewhat extend the duration of the song buffs."/>
                </StackLayout>
            </Frame>
        </StackLayout>
    </ScrollView>
</ContentPage>